# HNG Stage 1b - Interactive Profile Card

A fully responsive, accessible, and semantic Profile Card component built for the HNG i14 Internship. 

🔗 **[Live Demo on Vercel](https://stage-1-profilecard.vercel.app/)**

## 📌 Project Overview
This project serves as a digital identity card/portfolio widget. It is built strictly with vanilla web technologies, focusing heavily on semantic HTML structuring, WCAG accessibility standards, and basic DOM manipulation to render a live-updating epoch timestamp.

## ✨ Features & Requirements Met
- **Semantic HTML5:** Built using meaningful landmarks (`<article>`, `<header>`, `<figure>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`) rather than nested generic divs.
- **Accessibility (a11y) Focus:**
  - Includes meaningful `alt` text for the avatar.
  - The live time update container utilizes `aria-live="polite"` so screen readers can announce changes without interrupting the user.
  - High color contrast ratios to ensure readability.
  - External links utilize `target="_blank"` paired with `rel="noopener noreferrer"` for security and privacy.
- **Real-Time Data:** Features a custom JavaScript interval engine that fetches and displays the current Epoch time in milliseconds (`Date.now()`), refreshing seamlessly on the UI.
- **Responsive Layout:** Adapts beautifully from 320px mobile screens up to wide desktop monitors using modern CSS layouts.
- **Automated Testing Ready:** All required `data-testid` attributes have been strictly implemented.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **HTML5:** Semantic structure and accessibility markers.
- **CSS3:** Custom properties for theme management, responsive media queries, and modern UI styling.
- **Vanilla JavaScript (ES6):** Live epoch time rendering engine.

## 🚀 Running Locally
To view this project locally, clone the repository and open the `index.html` file in your browser. 

```bash
git clone https://github.com/bukola2005/STAGE-1-profilecard
cd STAGE 1 PROFILECARD
# Open index.html in your preferred browser